name: #09 CBD
description: Cannabidiol (CBD) has no psychoactive properties because does not directly bind to cannabinoid receptors. CBD is legal, so CBD oils can be bought and used without fear in many countries. Although the scheme of its action in our bodies causes a lot of problems to science, it undoubtedly has a few beneficial properties, as when fighting the symptoms of premenstrual syndrome, in relieving chronic pain, in the case of anxiety disorders, in the treatment of cancer because stimulates apoptosis or the programmed death of cancer cells, in eliminating stress, in inflammation, in the case of dementia and neurodegenerative diseases, e.g. multiple sclerosis.
